{{Quote|A powerful sorcerer who gave himself to an ancient entity... can bend the very laws of physics, tried very hard to kill me.|[[Doctor Strange]] to [[Christine Palmer]]|Doctor Strange (film)}}
*'''Master Martial Artist''': [[File:Ancient One DS Death.png|thumb|250px|Kaecilius fighting against the [[Ancient One]]]] Kaecilius is a highly skilled and formidable martial artist. He maintained the upper hand in his duel with [[Stephen Strange]] and was only defeated after Strange managed to trap him. Kaecilius also held his own the longest out of the [[Zealots]] in the second fight against the [[Ancient One]] and even managed to ultimately surprise and kill her, although he needed the Ancient One to be distracted in fighting one of the Zealots to pull off such a feat. In the final fight, Kaecilius used his martial arts skill to battle Strange again and despite Strange using the reconstructing environment to his advantage, Kaecilius seemingly maintained the upper hand, forcing Strange to secure a bargain with [[Dormammu]].
*'''Sword Mastery''': Due to his former training as the [[Masters of the Mystic Arts|Master of The Mystic Arts]], Kaecillius became a highly skilled user of swords, being able to use them to deliver countless attacks against [[Doctor Strange]], being able to subdue him easily until he was stopped by the [[Cloak of Levitation]], who made Strange trap him with a magical chain. One of the swords that he used to great extent was a [[Space-Time Shard]] that he could conjure at any time.
*'''Knife Mastery''': Due to his former training as the [[Masters of the Mystic Arts|Master of The Mystic Arts]], Kaecillius became a highly skilled user of knives and [[Scythe Daggers]], being able to use them to deliver a fatal attack against the likes of the powerful [[Ancient One]]. He used his daggers to decapitate the [[Kamar-Taj Librarian]].
{{Quote|His disciples followed him like sheep. Seduced by false doctrine.|[[Karl Mordo]] to [[Stephen Strange]]|Doctor Strange (film)}}
*'''Master Tactician''': [[File:Theft of the Book of Cagliostro 14.png|thumb|250px|Kaecilius leading the [[Zealots]]]] Kaecilius led a revolt against the [[Ancient One]] and the [[Masters of the Mystic Arts]] which gave him many followers who walked out of [[Kamar-Taj]]. The group, named the [[Zealots]], were led by Kaecilius to obtain eternal life by [[Dormammu]]. However, Kaecilius was not perfect at planning, as he didn't foresee Dormmamu's betrayal, turning them all into [[Mindless Ones]].
*'''Bilingualism''': Kaecilius is fluent in his native English, as well as [[Nelvayu]] while performing the ritual from the [[Book of Cagliostro]] to contact Dormammu.

